                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No.3382/19.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Josse Ten Noode</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Wilson reports that the title of the new King of Belgium will be Albert I,
                    and that the ceremony of enthronement will take place on the 23d instant. He
                    adds that the diplomatists will be received on the 24th.</p>
            </div>
